# SEQUENCE 10 — THE BOWL BEYOND ITS OWNER

/* TRACE: FU-056 | SC-151 */

EXT. KANCHI — FAMINE RELIEF CAMP — MORNING #66#

The Amudhasurabhi is present.

But it is not the whole solution.

People organise water.

Others cook.

Others translate needs.

Others care for those who cannot reach the line.

The miracle has become a responsibility shared.

/* TRACE: FU-057 | SC-152 */

INT. RELIEF HALL — DAY #67#

A person asks Manimekalai where the vessel truly belongs.

MANIMEKALAI

Wherever compassion does not need ownership.

She gives instructions, not commands.

The workers continue without waiting for her.

/* TRACE: FU-058 | SC-153 */

EXT. CITY EDGE — SUNSET #68#

Madhavi, Sudhamathi and Chitrapathi watch the city change.

Each understands Manimekalai differently.

None owns her.

/* TRACE: FU-059 | SC-154 */

INT. QUIET COURTYARD — NIGHT #69#

Manimekalai sits alone.

She remembers everyone whose hunger brought her here.

Not as a burden.

As a connection.

/* TRACE: FU-060 | SC-155 */

EXT. KANCHI — PUBLIC ROAD — DAWN #70#

The relief system continues.

The vessel passes between hands.

The camera stays with the people receiving and giving.

Not the object.

/* TRACE: FU-061 | SC-156 */

EXT. SEA HORIZON — MORNING #71#

Aputhiran's image returns briefly.

Not as a ghost.

As a question answered.

Compassion survived because it changed form.

/* TRACE: FU-062 | SC-157 */

EXT. KANCHI — FEEDING SPACE — DAY #72#

Manimekalai walks away from the centre of the gathering.

No one follows because they are dependent on her.

They continue because they learned together.

The bowl remains.

The owner disappears.

The service continues.

FADE OUT.

END.